Name: 85, Bullsbrook
Description: Poor visibility when turning onto 1 from 85, especially turning right. Traffic turning left onto 85 from 1 block the view of traffic waiting to turn right onto 1 from 85. I have seen many near accidents where cars have pulled out and not seen the traffic travelling north on 1. On one occasion when a car pulled out turning right onto 1, a Ute had to swerve onto the other side of the road to avoid hitting the car, the Ute veered off the road before gaining control. Luckily no oncoming traffic.
Comment 2: Cherie: there have been numerous accidents at the intersection from small fender benders to head on collisions.  When turning right onto Gt Northen Hwy, it is impossible to see past vehicles in the left turning lane and when turning left onto Gt Northern Hwy (off Rutland) it is impossible to see past vehicles waiting to turn right.  Its a very busy intersection and the speed limit is 90.  I think they need to put lights or a roundabout or they need to re-alighn the whole intersectiion.
Comment 3: Tony: Number of accidents have been at this intersection Rutland Rd and Great Northern Highway.No room for a large truck to do a right hand turn into Rutland Rd if a vehicle is at the intersection waiting to do a right hand turn on to Great Northern Hwy also your vision is block when a vehicle is waiting to turn left on to Great Northern Hwy.There is a stop sign there majority of drivers ignore it.
Comment 5: Diane: Numerous traffic accidents and near misses. The road needs lights or a roundabout to make it safer.
Comment 9: Glenn: High speed traffic in both directions including large trucks. Limited opportunity at peak times to turn right across from the T intersetion causing frustration and increasing risk of accidents.
Comment 12: Lois: there has been many accidents at this intersection - great northern highway and rutland road..near misses all the time in peak traffic hours..ithink there has maybe been one fatal..
Comment 23: Death defying moves to get into traffic on gst northern highway.
Comment 29: Natalie: Impatient drivers who can�۪t wait and cut across vehicles at high speeds including heavy vehicles. There is also poor road markings which make drivers inadvertently cut the corner. Poor visibility behind turning vehicles when turning onto the highway.
Comment 36: Carol: Near misses and lots of accidents at this intersection
Comment 38: There are lots of blind spots when trying to turn onto Great Northern Highway. There have been numerous crashes there.
Comment 39: cars pulling out in front of you from stop sign as they can't see you or there is poor opportunity for them to get out so they risk it
Comment 41: John: Very high incidents of crashes or near misses. Vehicles Turing from stop sign have blind spots or run the stop sign to get out onto Grt Northern Hwy.
